    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-27T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.24/150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-27T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 27, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>323. Your 351, February 16, 9 a.m. Personal for the Minister from Wallace Murray.
                    I regret that the military authorities have <pb facs="0080" n="68"
                        xml:id="pg_68"/> found it impossible to make available the two planes
                    desired for the use of Misr Air Lines. I am convinced, however, that the
                    military authorities have gone into the question very carefully but found it
                    impossible to furnish the planes at the present time because of the very urgent
                    need of our Armed Forces for planes of this type. [Murray.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
